KAISER PERMANENTE, Oakland, Calif., said it plans a public offering of $150 million 9% notes, due Nov. 1, 2001.
The notes, which are exempt from regular Securities and Exchange Commission registration, are the co-obligation of Kaiser Foundation Hospitals and the Kaiser Foundation Health Plan Inc. Lead underwriter will be First Boston Corp. Proceeds will be used for general organizational purposes, including repayment of some short-term borrowings, which were used to finance capital expenditures, the health maintenance organization said. 

